The '''California Insurance Equality Act''' (AB 2208) <ref>[http://www.eqca.org/atf/cf/%7B34F258B3-8482-4943-91CB-08C4B0246A88%7D/AB%202208%20FAQ.pdf THE CALIFORNIA INSURANCE EQUALITY ACT: HOW TO USE IT AND WHAT IT MEANS FOR YOU AND YOUR FAMILY]</ref><ref>[http://www.leginfo.ca.gov/pub/03-04/bill/asm/ab_2201-2250/ab_2208_bill_20040913_chaptered.html Full Text AB 2208]</ref> is a state [[law]] that requires [[California]] [[insurance]] providers and managed care plans ([[Health maintenance organization|HMO]]s) to provide coverage for registered [[Domestic partnership in California|domestic partners]] that is equal to spousal coverage.<ref name="dpb21">{{harvnb|Solomon|2006|p=21}}</ref> The law complements the California Domestic Partnership Rights and Responsibilities Act of 2003 <ref>[http://www.assembly.ca.gov/lgbt_caucus/laws/2003/ab0205/fulltextchapteredbill.htm Full Text AB 205] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110510010252/http://www.assembly.ca.gov/LGBT_Caucus/laws/2003/ab0205/fulltextchapteredbill.htm |date=2011-05-10 }}</ref> (AB 205), which grants registered domestic partners most of the same rights and responsibilities under California law as they belong to married couples.
==Impact== Prior to enactment of AB 2208, California law required insurance providers to provide benefits to domestic partners as [[Dependant|dependents]]. The California Insurance Equality Act now requires domestic partners to be covered as spouses.<ref>[http://www.unmarriedamerica.org/members/news/2004/November-DP/cal_health_mandate.htm California health insurers mandated to offer domestic partner coverage]</ref> The act also prohibits employers from asking for more proof of partnership of domestic partners than they ask of spouses.<ref name="dpb21" /> This Act should render insurance benefits payable to domestic partners more easily, without reference to inconsistent and confusing statutory and case law definitions of what constitutes a “dependent” under California law.<ref>[http://www.gjel.com/news/california-insurance-equality-act.html The California Insurance Equality Act: Real Change or Window Dressing?]</ref><ref>[http://www.preceptgroup.com/company/news/article.aspx?PRPRI=20.article&archiveyear=2004 California Insurance Equality Act - Domestic Partner Coverage]</ref> The act also prohibits employers from asking for more proof of partnership of domestic partners than they ask of spouses.<ref>[http://jonesday.com/2005-california-employment-law-legislative-update-03-22-2005/ 2005 California Employment Law Legislative Update]</ref> However, some types of employee benefit plans are exempt from the law.<ref>[http://www.shrm.org/hrdisciplines/benefits/Articles/Pages/CaliforniaRuling.aspx California's Ban on Same-Sex Marriage Held Unconstitutional]</ref>
